<TITLE> BNP leader assaulted in Bhola </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, Apr 15 (bdnews24.com)  Former BNP MP Nazim Uddin Alam was assaulted allegedly by ruling Awami League activists during an election campaign in Bhola. Alam told bdnews24.com that some local AL leaders assaulted him and other party men while he was running a campaign for BNP candidate Hafiz Uddin Ahmed for the upcoming by polls at Farashganj Union of Lalmohan upazila. "Brickbats hurled by them cracked my head," Alam said. Seven other people, also injured are  Maminul Haque Pintu, 35, Jamal, 32, Chinu Mia, 35, Shahidul Islam, 32, Sajeeb, 30, Billal, 25 and Ibrahim, 30. They are undergoing treatment at the upazila health complex. bdne
